Breastfeeding is a phase of life in which every mom faces difficulty in.🙈It just revolves around so much of stress when it comes to breast feeding. Dilemmas like feeding baby every two hours or baby never latching properly or low milk supply are just some of it. Every mom goes through one of this phase regardless of the number of pregnancies she had. 

After my first pregnancy, I thought of using my first breast pump with Viara. Unfortunately, it was a manual pump and it was kind of difficult for me. Looking at my struggle, I was recommended an electric breast pump by one of my friends. And I am more than grateful for this recommendation.✨

So my first electric breast pump was of @philipsavent_india and it was for Viara. And to my surprise, now phillips has launched a new product which is really very handy.

💫It is very easy to use and the suction is similar to baby sucking which makes it a painless process. 
💫It is portable and very easy to carry.

So if you are someone who is stuck with these challenges then i would highly recommend you to have an electric breast pump. Whenever you feel like you're tired or you want to go out or you want to have your me time and when you're stressed about the breast feed you can easily pump and store the milk before hand. I'm sure many of you have seen my stories where I have pumped the milk and stepped out. 

So do checkout the Phillips Avent Breast Pump! 💕 It's a saviour for mumma's!

latestIgtvVideos.title: Being a lifecell user
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I clearly remember that day when I was in my 7th month of pregnancy with Viara. During the doctor's visit, we came across a flyer at Masran's clinic & was curious to know more. We always consult our doctor friends before making medical or health-related decisions & surprisingly, both our friends had done stem cell banking for their kids with @lifecellin Thus, without a second thought, we wanted to do it for our little one too & give her “a gift of a lifetime."

Research has shown that stem cells extracted from the umbilical cord that connects the mother and the baby can help in treating 80+ disorders. Plus the collection process is painless and risk-free for both the mother & the baby! The best part with LifeCell Community Banking is that stem cells can be used for the entire family (parents, siblings, & both maternal & paternal grandparents). So, it’s like health meets convenience! 

As shown in the video, the online enrolment process is very simple. You will also get guaranteed cashback worth Rs 20k depending on the chosen storage plan and if you use my code VIV2000, you will get an additional Rs 2K discount! 

If you have any questions, type in the comments section &  I'll be glad to answer!

Visit www.lifecell.in

@lifecellin
x
@supergalviv

latestPosts.caption:
From Not knowing what startup is to building @myburgo_app

It all started 10 years ago.
2014.

I was fresh out of M.Tech, full of dreams and curiosity.
I got my first job with a ₹15K salary, no idea what a startup even meant.
But there I was — doing it all.
Coding. Testing. Sales. Support.
Just me, figuring it out as I went.

I didn’t have it all mapped out…
But I knew one thing: I loved building.
Building systems. Building ideas.
And someday… building something of my own.

Fast forward to now — I’m still building.
But this time, it’s not just software.
It’s something closer to my heart.

✨ It’s @myburgo_app
a platform born out of my own parenting journey,
where I wanted to create something meaningful for moms like me.

From writing code to writing captions,
From tech meetings to therapy workshops —
My journey has changed, but my passion hasn’t.

I still love creating.
Only now… it’s not just about what I build,
It’s about who I’m building it for. 💛

Link for app is in bio .
I would love to know your feedback 

#MyStory #WomenInTech #Mompreneur #MyBurgo #BuiltWithHeart #FromCodeToCare
